rComments: Awesome prof
Friendly
Very clear on what she expects, gives good feedback on proposals to help you improve on the final essay. If you go to class she basically tells you what's on the grammar quiz. Great prof altogether.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: This course is definitely not the easiest course but the professor made everything so easy. Highly recommend her.

Fantastic Professor! She is very professional but also made a few jokes here and there to keep things light. Her class is easy! In part because it is light on content, no final exam just a final report, but also because she is very clear about her expectations and she prepares you very well for each assignment. She is also a very fair grader!
She's a caring and funny professor who makes course expectations clear.

Super easy class! She understands that the course is boring and tries to make it interesting :) 2 quizzes, 2 assignments, and a take home final (all super easy) if you go to class she'll tell you EXACTLY what will be on the quiz
Easiest class ever taken.

Very easy class, super light work load, you just have to make sure you keep track of when things are due. Lectures are not mandatory, she posts everything online and everything from the quizzes are in the slides.

Took Professor Morrissey for Technical Report Writing as a requirement in 1st year engineering. Best professor teaching the course by far! Easiest A+ with the least amount of work possible. Only need to focus on 1 report the whole semester and the quizzes are straight from the powerpoint.

Amazing professor that knows a lot about her subjects. She's funny and is bound to make you smile. With that said, lectures are not mandatory for success and minimal notes need to be taken. Simply reading the slides and writing clear and concisely will ensure you do well!

Explains clearly everything you need to know/do on assignments and quizzes. Quizzes are based solely on lecture presentations. Discussion groups are mostly open sessions. Very organized. Highly recommend her. Little amount of work, so each task worth a lot. Easy marker.
Easiest course you'll ever attend, no work and easy.

The lecture content itself is a little boring, but she tries to finish it as fast as she can. You just need to write 2 quizzes (the content is very clear on her lecture notes posted online), no final exam (write a report in advance at home and bring it on a certain day). And she also provide a model report. You can absolutely imitate it.

The course is very boring and easy, but she does her best to teach it. Only one lecture per week, two easy quizzes and two very easy assignments, but start your final report early instead of having to write 15 pages during exam season. I did badly in every high school English course but this was a breeze.
By far the easiest prof for this class. You can not attend class and easily get an A+.
Horrifically boring class, but she does her best to make it bearable. Next to no coursework aside from the final report and much easier grading than high school english.
super nice and helpful, makes herself very clear. boring course but helpful

Take your technical report writing with her! She is absolutely amazing. You will most likely be bored during lectures but that's because the material is so dull. There will be 2 tests that are easy A's plus a paper that will require work but is still aceable.
Took it for engineering. She's the easiest english teacher (because there are a lot)! Ridiculously easy and a complete bird course. The course is very boring but she's really chill.
Very clear prof, read her lectures and youll be good to go. Work on the final report throughout the semester so you dont have too much to do near the end. Quizes are super easy and worth 30%.

She is honestly the best prof. You could ever ask for! Very straight forward,  listen to her lectures and review them as a lot of them end up on the mid terms and she's super friendly. She makes her expectations SUPER clear listen to her and review your notes and you could end with an A+ (Also Don't save your report to the last day like I did)
The only real work in this course was the final report, the prof is very clear (english prof) and helpful. but be careful not to miss a quiz like I did since each is worth 15%

The nice thing about her is she's the type of Professor who knows her stuff and teaches it well. Spots to get in her class are race, really! The only problem is that she teaches a very dry subject so it would be quite obvious if her classes seem dull in interest.
very good prof, very helpful, nice about this prof is that there are only two quizzes which are grammar from high school   and a final report were she isn't strict  in giving the mark
Great prof, definetly got me more interested in english. if you have her you are very lucky. all around great prof

Great class! She rewards those who attend and participate! The lectures were always pretty interactive and the readings were interesting. The midterm and final were extremly easy if you attended class and did the readings. The only downside was that her essay topics were pretty difficult and demanding. Take her class! It was great!

Great Prof. Nice Lady. Easy marker. Easy midterms. She gives everyone a fair opportunity to do well in her course. If you attend the lectures and read the stories, you'll do great. The stories were relatively easy and the novels were short.

Fabulous professor. She goes out of her way to help her students and makes class as interesting as possible. Both the midterm and final were extremely easy as were the papers. I would recommend trying to GET INTO her class, believe me its worth it A+
EASY! we read lik e8 short stories the whole semester, and her novels are kids novels! midterm and final EXTREMELY easy ( like easy A+)but she makes papers hard so it balances out.
